Tonight, top politicians have heeded president Uhuru Kenyatta's ban on political gatherings and cancelled all planned rallies until further notice. some including Wiper Party have however announced new strategies of campaigning for their candidate in the upcoming by elections. Wiper party leader Kalonzo Musyoka says they will now do drive past in areas where they had planned to hold rallies for their candidate in the machakos senatorial race. and as Patrick Amimo reports, politicians have been viewed as the super spreaders of covid 19 as they hold huge rallies without observing covid 19 containment protocols